frDteRowStatusTable.name: frDteRowStatusTable
frDteRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDte components.

frDteRowStatusEntry.name: frDteRowStatusEntry
frDteRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDte component.

frDteRowStatus.name: frDteRowStatus
frDteRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDte components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteComponentName.name: frDteComponentName
frDteComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteStorageType.name: frDteStorageType
frDteStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDte tables.

frDteIndex.name: frDteIndex
frDteIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDte tables.

frDteCidDataTable.name: frDteCidDataTable
frDteCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

frDteCustomerIdentifier.name: frDteCustomerIdentifier
frDteCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

frDteIfEntryTable.name: frDteIfEntryTable
frDteIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

frDteIfAdminStatus.name: frDteIfAdminStatus
frDteIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

frDteIfIndex.name: frDteIfIndex
frDteIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

frDteProvTable.name: frDteProvTable
frDteProvTable.description: This group contains the provisioned attributes for the FrDte component.

frDteAcceptUndefinedDlci.name: frDteAcceptUndefinedDlci
frDteAcceptUndefinedDlci.description: This parameter allows previously undefined Data Link Connection Identifiers (DLCIs) to be dynamically accepted in the default remote group. If set to enabled, undefined DLCIs will be accepted, if disabled, they will not.

frDteStateTable.name: frDteStateTable
frDteStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

frDteAdminState.name: frDteAdminState
frDteAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

frDteOperationalState.name: frDteOperationalState
frDteOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

frDteUsageState.name: frDteUsageState
frDteUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

frDteOperStatusTable.name: frDteOperStatusTable
frDteOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

frDteSnmpOperStatus.name: frDteSnmpOperStatus
frDteSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

frDteOperTable.name: frDteOperTable
frDteOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes for the FrDte component.

frDteLinkOperState.name: frDteLinkOperState
frDteLinkOperState.description: This attribute describes the operational state of the Link Control protocol. If the interface to the physical link hardware is inactive, the linkOperState is in the down state. The polling state only occurs when the Local Management Interface (LMI) is enabled and the physical link is active. The polling state indicates LMI is polling for its peer. Once communication is established the linkOperState will transition to the active state. If the procedure attribute of the Lmi component is set to none, linkOperState will transition to the active state once the physical link becomes active.

frDteErrTable.name: frDteErrTable
frDteErrTable.description: This group contains the SNMP frErrEntry attributes for the FrDte component.

frDteErrType.name: frDteErrType
frDteErrType.description: The type of error that was last seen on this interface. The error types are as follows: receiveShort: This error indicates a received frame was discarded because it was less than four octets long or it was missing the Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) for a SNAP header. receiveLong: This error indicates a received frame was discarded because it was longer than expected. This error is currently not used on this interface. illegalDlci: This error indicates that a received frame was discarded because it's Q.922 address was not two octets in length. This error could also indicate that a frame was discarded because it was received on a DLCI reserved for LMI which had not been provisioned active. dlcmiProtoErr: This error indicates an LMI frame was received with contents formatted incorrectly. dlcmiUnknownIe: This error indicates that an LMI frame was received which contained an unsupported Information Element (IE) type dlcmiSequenceErr: This error indicates that an LMI frame was received whose Keep Alive Sequence was incorrect. dlcmiUnknownRpt: This error indicates that an LMI frame was received which contained a Report-type Information Element with an invalid type of report. noErrorSinceReset: This error type indicates that there has not been an error since the interface has been reset. unknownError: This error type contains the cumulation of receive frame errors that did not fit one of the MIB error descriptions above. These errors include those counted by the following attributes: ulpUnknownProtocol - A received frame was discarded because the Upper Level Protocol (ULP) encapsulation used was unsupported. badFc - A received frame was discarded because the frame control character was incorrect. defragSequenceErrors - A fragment was received which was discarded due to an out of sequence error detection.

frDteErrData.name: frDteErrData
frDteErrData.description: An octet string containing the first part of the frame in which an error was last detected.

frDteErrTime.name: frDteErrTime
frDteErrTime.description: The time at which the last error was detected and recorded in errType.

frDteErrDiscards.name: frDteErrDiscards
frDteErrDiscards.description: Number of inbound frames dropped because of format errors or because the virtual circuit was not known. Format errors, in this case, are any errors which would prevent the system from recognizing the DLCI and placing the error in the discard category. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteErrFaults.name: frDteErrFaults
frDteErrFaults.description: This attribute counts the number of times LMI has taken down the interface. When the procedure attribute of the Lmi component is set to none, this counter will not be incremented. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteErrFaultTime.name: frDteErrFaultTime
frDteErrFaultTime.description: The last time the errFaults counter was incremented.

frDteErrStatsTable.name: frDteErrStatsTable
frDteErrStatsTable.description: This group contains error counters for the FrDte.

frDteXmitDiscardPvcDown.name: frDteXmitDiscardPvcDown
frDteXmitDiscardPvcDown.description: Count of transmitted frames discarded because the Dlci or a component positioned in a hierarchically fashion above it (e.g. it's remote group or the FrDte component) was administratively disabled. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteXmitDiscardLmiInactive.name: frDteXmitDiscardLmiInactive
frDteXmitDiscardLmiInactive.description: Count of transmitted frames discarded because the Local Management Interface (LMI) was not yet active (i.e. LMI was still in the polling state). This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteXmitDiscardFramerDown.name: frDteXmitDiscardFramerDown
frDteXmitDiscardFramerDown.description: Count of transmitted frames discarded because the framer component was down. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteXmitDiscardPvcInactive.name: frDteXmitDiscardPvcInactive
frDteXmitDiscardPvcInactive.description: Count of transmitted frames discarded because the Local Management Interface (LMI) had inactivated or invalidated the Dlci. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteXmitDiscardCirExceeded.name: frDteXmitDiscardCirExceeded
frDteXmitDiscardCirExceeded.description: Count of transmitted frames discarded because CIR was enabled on a Dlci without a HibernationQueue subcomponent and the traffic exceeded the combined Committed and Excess Burst thresholds. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteRecvDiscardPvcDown.name: frDteRecvDiscardPvcDown
frDteRecvDiscardPvcDown.description: Count of received frames discarded because the Dlci or a component positioned in a hierarchically fashion above it (e.g. it's remote group or the FrDte component) was administratively disabled. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteRecvDiscardLmiInactive.name: frDteRecvDiscardLmiInactive
frDteRecvDiscardLmiInactive.description: Count of received frames discarded because the Local Management Interface (LMI) was not yet active (i.e. LMI was still in the polling state). This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteRecvDiscardPvcInactive.name: frDteRecvDiscardPvcInactive
frDteRecvDiscardPvcInactive.description: Count of received frames discarded because the Local Management Interface (LMI) had inactivated or invalidated the Dlci. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteBadFc.name: frDteBadFc
frDteBadFc.description: Count of received frames discarded because the frame control character was incorrect. This may indicate that the other side of the link is configured for a different link level protocol. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteUlpUnknownProtocol.name: frDteUlpUnknownProtocol
frDteUlpUnknownProtocol.description: Count of received frames discarded because the Upper Level Protocol (ULP) encapsulation used was unsupported. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDefragSequenceErrors.name: frDteDefragSequenceErrors
frDteDefragSequenceErrors.description: Count of fragments received which were discarded due to out of sequence error detection. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteReceiveShort.name: frDteReceiveShort
frDteReceiveShort.description: Count of received frames (including LMI frames) discarded because they were less than four octets long or they were missing the Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) for a SNAP header. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteIllegalDlci.name: frDteIllegalDlci
frDteIllegalDlci.description: Count of received frames discarded because their Q.922 address was not two octets in length. This count also includes frames discarded because they were received on a Dlci reserved for LMI which had not been provisioned active. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlcmiProtoErr.name: frDteDlcmiProtoErr
frDteDlcmiProtoErr.description: Count of received LMI frames whose contents were formatted incorrectly. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlcmiUnknownIe.name: frDteDlcmiUnknownIe
frDteDlcmiUnknownIe.description: Count of received LMI frames which contained an unsupported Information Element (IE) type. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlcmiSequenceErr.name: frDteDlcmiSequenceErr
frDteDlcmiSequenceErr.description: Count of received LMI frames whose Keep Alive Sequence was incorrect. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlcmiUnknownRpt.name: frDteDlcmiUnknownRpt
frDteDlcmiUnknownRpt.description: Count of received LMI frames which contained a Report-type Information Element with an invalid type of report. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteFramerRowStatusTable.name: frDteFramerRowStatusTable
frDteFramerRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteFramer components.

frDteFramerRowStatusEntry.name: frDteFramerRowStatusEntry
frDteFramerRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteFramer component.

frDteFramerRowStatus.name: frDteFramerRowStatus
frDteFramerRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteFramer components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteFramerComponentName.name: frDteFramerComponentName
frDteFramerComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteFramerStorageType.name: frDteFramerStorageType
frDteFramerStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteFramer tables.

frDteFramerIndex.name: frDteFramerIndex
frDteFramerIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteFramer tables.

frDteFramerProvTable.name: frDteFramerProvTable
frDteFramerProvTable.description: This group contains the base provisioning data for the Framer component. Application or hardware interface specific provisioning data is contained in other provisional Framer groups.

frDteFramerInterfaceName.name: frDteFramerInterfaceName
frDteFramerInterfaceName.description: This attribute contains a hardware component name. The attribute associates the application with a specific link. This defines the module processor on which Framer's parent component (as well as Framer itself) will run.

frDteFramerStateTable.name: frDteFramerStateTable
frDteFramerStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

frDteFramerAdminState.name: frDteFramerAdminState
frDteFramerAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

frDteFramerOperationalState.name: frDteFramerOperationalState
frDteFramerOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

frDteFramerUsageState.name: frDteFramerUsageState
frDteFramerUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

frDteFramerStatsTable.name: frDteFramerStatsTable
frDteFramerStatsTable.description: This group contains the operational statistics data for a Framer component.

frDteFramerFrmToIf.name: frDteFramerFrmToIf
frDteFramerFrmToIf.description: This attribute counts the number of frames transmitted to the link interface by Framer. Note: This does not include the number of frames transmitted directly to the hardware queue, thus bypassing the Framer component.

frDteFramerFrmFromIf.name: frDteFramerFrmFromIf
frDteFramerFrmFromIf.description: This attribute counts the number of frames received from the link interface by Framer.

frDteFramerAborts.name: frDteFramerAborts
frDteFramerAborts.description: This attribute counts the total number of aborts received.

frDteFramerCrcErrors.name: frDteFramerCrcErrors
frDteFramerCrcErrors.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames with CRC errors.

frDteFramerLrcErrors.name: frDteFramerLrcErrors
frDteFramerLrcErrors.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames with LRC errors.

frDteFramerNonOctetErrors.name: frDteFramerNonOctetErrors
frDteFramerNonOctetErrors.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames that were non octet aligned.

frDteFramerOverruns.name: frDteFramerOverruns
frDteFramerOverruns.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames received from the link for which overruns occurred.

frDteFramerUnderruns.name: frDteFramerUnderruns
frDteFramerUnderruns.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames transmitted to the link for which underruns occurred.

frDteFramerLargeFrmErrors.name: frDteFramerLargeFrmErrors
frDteFramerLargeFrmErrors.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames received which were too large. The frame exceeded the maximumFrameLengthLimit provisioned attribute or it contained more than the 255 block hardware limit.

frDteFramerUtilTable.name: frDteFramerUtilTable
frDteFramerUtilTable.description: This group contains the link utilization operational data for a Framer component.

frDteFramerNormPrioLinkUtilToIf.name: frDteFramerNormPrioLinkUtilToIf
frDteFramerNormPrioLinkUtilToIf.description: This attribute is the utilization of the normal priority data sent to the link as a percentage of the available bandwidth on the link. The utilization is the average for the last minute.

frDteFramerNormPrioLinkUtilFromIf.name: frDteFramerNormPrioLinkUtilFromIf
frDteFramerNormPrioLinkUtilFromIf.description: This attribute is the utilization of the normal priority data received from the link as a percentage of the available bandwidth on the link. The utilization is the average for the last minute.

frDteLmiRowStatusTable.name: frDteLmiRowStatusTable
frDteLmiRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteLmi components.

frDteLmiRowStatusEntry.name: frDteLmiRowStatusEntry
frDteLmiRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteLmi component.

frDteLmiRowStatus.name: frDteLmiRowStatus
frDteLmiRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteLmi components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

frDteLmiComponentName.name: frDteLmiComponentName
frDteLmiComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteLmiStorageType.name: frDteLmiStorageType
frDteLmiStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteLmi tables.

frDteLmiIndex.name: frDteLmiIndex
frDteLmiIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteLmi tables.

frDteLmiProvTable.name: frDteLmiProvTable
frDteLmiProvTable.description: This group contains the provisioned attributes for the Lmi component.

frDteLmiProcedures.name: frDteLmiProcedures
frDteLmiProcedures.description: This attribute selects the Local Management Interface (LMI) protocol to be used on the interface. This attribute is equivalent to the SNMP variable frDlcmiState. The vendorForum LMI protocol automatically implies that the DLCI used by the protocol is 1023. The ansi (T1.617 Annex D) and itu (ITU-T Recommendation Q.933 Annex A) LMI protocols use DLCI 0. If none is selected, no LMI procedures will run on the interface. Note that the ITU-T Recommendation Q.933 was previously a CCITT recommendation.

frDteLmiPollingInterval.name: frDteLmiPollingInterval
frDteLmiPollingInterval.description: This is the number of seconds between successive status enquiry messages. This field corresponds to the parameter T391 described in the ANSI T1.617-1991 Annex D.

frDteLmiFullEnquiryInterval.name: frDteLmiFullEnquiryInterval
frDteLmiFullEnquiryInterval.description: The count of status polls before a full status enquiry message is issued. Every nth poll will request a full status. This field corresponds to the parameter N391 described in the ANSI T1.617-1991 Annex D.

frDteLmiErrorThreshold.name: frDteLmiErrorThreshold
frDteLmiErrorThreshold.description: The number of errors detected within the monitored events window before declaring the link non-functional. This field corresponds to the parameter N392 described in the ANSI T1.617-1991 Annex D.

frDteLmiMonitoredEvents.name: frDteLmiMonitoredEvents
frDteLmiMonitoredEvents.description: The number of status polling intervals over which the errorthreshold is counted This is used to determine if the errorThreshold is exceeded. This field corresponds to the parameter N393 described in the ANSI T1.617-1991 Annex D.

frDteLmiOperTable.name: frDteLmiOperTable
frDteLmiOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes for the Lmi component.

frDteLmiLmiStatus.name: frDteLmiLmiStatus
frDteLmiLmiStatus.description: This indicates the status of the Frame Relay interface as determined by the performance of the link management interface (LMI). If no LMI is running, lmiStatus will stay in the running state indefinitely.

frDteRgRowStatusTable.name: frDteRgRowStatusTable
frDteRgRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteRg components.

frDteRgRowStatusEntry.name: frDteRgRowStatusEntry
frDteRgRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteRg component.

frDteRgRowStatus.name: frDteRgRowStatus
frDteRgRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteRg components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteRgComponentName.name: frDteRgComponentName
frDteRgComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteRgStorageType.name: frDteRgStorageType
frDteRgStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteRg tables.

frDteRgIndex.name: frDteRgIndex
frDteRgIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteRg tables.

frDteRgIfEntryTable.name: frDteRgIfEntryTable
frDteRgIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

frDteRgIfAdminStatus.name: frDteRgIfAdminStatus
frDteRgIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

frDteRgIfIndex.name: frDteRgIfIndex
frDteRgIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

frDteRgProvTable.name: frDteRgProvTable
frDteRgProvTable.description: This group contains the provisioned attributes for the Remote Group component.

frDteRgMaxTransmissionUnit.name: frDteRgMaxTransmissionUnit
frDteRgMaxTransmissionUnit.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit size of the largest datagram (including Frame Relay header) which can be sent on the interface.

frDteRgMpTable.name: frDteRgMpTable
frDteRgMpTable.description: This group contains the base provisioning data for the Media Application component.

frDteRgLinkToProtocolPort.name: frDteRgLinkToProtocolPort
frDteRgLinkToProtocolPort.description: This attribute contains a protocol port component name. The attribute associates the application with a protocol port.

frDteRgStateTable.name: frDteRgStateTable
frDteRgStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

frDteRgOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

frDteRgUsageState.name: frDteRgUsageState
frDteRgUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

frDteRgOperStatusTable.name: frDteRgOperStatusTable
frDteRgOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

frDteRgSnmpOperStatus.name: frDteRgSnmpOperStatus
frDteRgSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

frDteRgLtDlciTable.name: frDteRgLtDlciTable
frDteRgLtDlciTable.description: This attribute associates a Rg component with zero or more StDlci components. The Rg and StDlci components must be under the same FrDte component.

frDteRgLtDlciValue.name: frDteRgLtDlciValue
frDteRgLtDlciValue.description: This variable represents both the value and the index for the frDteRgLtDlciTable.

frDteRgLtDlciRowStatus.name: frDteRgLtDlciRowStatus
frDteRgLtDlciRowStatus.description: This variable is used to control the addition and deletion of individual values of the frDteRgLtDlciTable.

frDteRgBfrRowStatusTable.name: frDteRgBfrRowStatusTable
frDteRgBfrRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteRgBfr components.

frDteRgBfrRowStatusEntry.name: frDteRgBfrRowStatusEntry
frDteRgBfrRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteRgBfr component.

frDteRgBfrRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteRgBfr components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteRgBfrComponentName.name: frDteRgBfrComponentName
frDteRgBfrComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteRgBfrStorageType.name: frDteRgBfrStorageType
frDteRgBfrStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteRgBfr tables.

frDteRgBfrIndex.name: frDteRgBfrIndex
frDteRgBfrIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteRgBfr tables.

frDteRgBfrProvTable.name: frDteRgBfrProvTable
frDteRgBfrProvTable.description: This group contains the provisioning attributes for the Bfr component.

frDteRgBfrMacType.name: frDteRgBfrMacType
frDteRgBfrMacType.description: This attribute specifies the MAC address type of the Bfr component. The value must be chosen based on the media of the traffic source. For traffic originated from FDDI, use fddi; for ethernet, use enet; for token ring, use tokenRing

frDteRgBfrBfrIndex.name: frDteRgBfrBfrIndex
frDteRgBfrBfrIndex.description: This attribute specifies the value which is used to derive a unique MAC address for the Bfr. The bfrIndex must be unique across all Bfrs on the same Lp.

frDteRgBfrOprTable.name: frDteRgBfrOprTable
frDteRgBfrOprTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes for the Bfr component..

frDteRgBfrMacAddr.name: frDteRgBfrMacAddr
frDteRgBfrMacAddr.description: This attribute indicates the unique MAC address of the Bfr component. This value is derived by the value of the attribute bfrIndex. The value is displayed as cannonical format.

frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatusTable.name: frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatusTable
frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteDynDlciDefs components.

frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatusEntry.name: frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatusEntry
frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteDynDlciDefs component.

frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatus.name: frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatus
frDteDynDlciDefsRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteDynDlciDefs components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

frDteDynDlciDefsComponentName.name: frDteDynDlciDefsComponentName
frDteDynDlciDefsComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteDynDlciDefsStorageType.name: frDteDynDlciDefsStorageType
frDteDynDlciDefsStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteDynDlciDefs tables.

frDteDynDlciDefsIndex.name: frDteDynDlciDefsIndex
frDteDynDlciDefsIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteDynDlciDefs tables.

frDteDynDlciDefsProvTable.name: frDteDynDlciDefsProvTable
frDteDynDlciDefsProvTable.description: This group contains the provisioned attributes for a virtual circuit. These attributes represent the default settings for the resulting Dlci components and can be operationally changed using the corresponding attributes under the Dlci component.

frDteDynDlciDefsStdRowStatus.name: frDteDynDlciDefsStdRowStatus
frDteDynDlciDefsStdRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to manage the status of a StDlci component. Set to active to enable the StDlci component. Set to notInService to disable the StDlci component. Set to createAndGo (SNMP only) to create a new StDlci component. Set to destroy (SNMP only) to delete an existing StDlci component.

frDteDynDlciDefsRateEnforcement.name: frDteDynDlciDefsRateEnforcement
frDteDynDlciDefsRateEnforcement.description: This attribute specifies whether the CIR attributes committedInformationRate, committedBurst, and excessBurst are used to define rate enforcement on this user DLCI. If rateEnforcement is enabled, and the combined Committed and Excess burst thresholds are exceeded, the frame in violation will be discarded immediately if a HibernationQueue subcomponent is not provisioned under the StDlci component. If a HibernationQueue is provisioned, the frame will be placed on the HibernationQueue at time of violation and transmission will be attempted later after the point at which the burst thresholds will no longer be exceeded. Setting all the CIR attributes to zero has the same affect as setting this attribute to disabled.

frDteDynDlciDefsCommittedInformationRate.name: frDteDynDlciDefsCommittedInformationRate
frDteDynDlciDefsCommittedInformationRate.description: The average number of bits to be transferred per second over the DLCI to the DCE. When this attribute is set to zero, the link speed will be used instead.

frDteDynDlciDefsCommittedBurst.name: frDteDynDlciDefsCommittedBurst
frDteDynDlciDefsCommittedBurst.description: The committed burst size (in bits) to which the DLCI wants to subscribe.

frDteDynDlciDefsExcessBurst.name: frDteDynDlciDefsExcessBurst
frDteDynDlciDefsExcessBurst.description: The excess burst size (in bits) to which the DLCI wants to subscribe.

frDteDynDlciDefsExcessBurstAction.name: frDteDynDlciDefsExcessBurstAction
frDteDynDlciDefsExcessBurstAction.description: This attribute specifies the action taken when the committedBurst size has been exceeded on the DLCI but the excessBurst size has not. If the attribute is set to setDeBit, the Discard Eligibility bit in the Frame Relay header will be turned on. If the attribute is set to none, no action will be taken.

frDteDynDlciDefsIpCos.name: frDteDynDlciDefsIpCos
frDteDynDlciDefsIpCos.description: This attribute specifies the initial Class of Service (CoS) given to each packet received on the on the virtual circuit identified by the dlci. The CoS value n is used to select Vr/<string> QosP/n. which determines the QualityofService-Profile to be used when the packet is forwarded. The intial CoS given to a packet by the assignedQoS attribute may be overriden when the cosPolicyAssignment attribute is defined on the IpPort or Ip components. When a packet is to be transmitted on a frDte protocol port where multiple virtual circuits are available for the packet's next hop, the packet is forwarded using the dlci where the ipCos value matches the CoS of the packet. When the packets's CoS does not match the ipCos value of any of the available virtual circuits, the packet will be forwarded using next lowest CoS; failing this, the packet will be forwarded using the next highest CoS.

frDteStDlciRowStatusTable.name: frDteStDlciRowStatusTable
frDteStDlciRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteStDlci components.

frDteStDlciRowStatusEntry.name: frDteStDlciRowStatusEntry
frDteStDlciRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteStDlci component.

frDteStDlciRowStatus.name: frDteStDlciRowStatus
frDteStDlciRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteStDlci components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteStDlciComponentName.name: frDteStDlciComponentName
frDteStDlciComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteStDlciStorageType.name: frDteStDlciStorageType
frDteStDlciStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteStDlci tables.

frDteStDlciIndex.name: frDteStDlciIndex
frDteStDlciIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteStDlci tables.

frDteStDlciProvTable.name: frDteStDlciProvTable
frDteStDlciProvTable.description: This group contains the provisioned attributes for a virtual circuit. These attributes represent the default settings for the resulting Dlci components and can be operationally changed using the corresponding attributes under the Dlci component.

frDteStDlciStdRowStatus.description: This attribute is used to manage the status of a StDlci component. Set to active to enable the StDlci component. Set to notInService to disable the StDlci component. Set to createAndGo (SNMP only) to create a new StDlci component. Set to destroy (SNMP only) to delete an existing StDlci component.

frDteStDlciRateEnforcement.name: frDteStDlciRateEnforcement
frDteStDlciRateEnforcement.description: This attribute specifies whether the CIR attributes committedInformationRate, committedBurst, and excessBurst are used to define rate enforcement on this user DLCI. frDteStDlciCommittedInformationRate.description: The average number of bits to be transferred per second over the DLCI to the DCE. When this attribute is set to zero, the link speed will be used instead.

frDteStDlciCommittedBurst.name: frDteStDlciCommittedBurst
frDteStDlciCommittedBurst.description: The committed burst size (in bits) to which the DLCI wants to subscribe.

frDteStDlciExcessBurst.name: frDteStDlciExcessBurst
frDteStDlciExcessBurst.description: The excess burst size (in bits) to which the DLCI wants to subscribe.

frDteStDlciExcessBurstAction.name: frDteStDlciExcessBurstAction
frDteStDlciExcessBurstAction.description: This attribute specifies the action taken when the committedBurst size has been exceeded on the DLCI but the excessBurst size has not. If the attribute is set to setDeBit, the Discard Eligibility bit in the Frame Relay header will be turned on. If the attribute is set to none, no action will be taken.

frDteStDlciIpCos.description: This attribute specifies the initial Class of Service (CoS) given to each packet received on the on the virtual circuit identified by the dlci. The CoS value n is used to select Vr/<string> QosP/n. which determines the QualityofService-Profile to be used when the packet is forwarded. The intial CoS given to a packet by the assignedQoS attribute may be overriden when the cosPolicyAssignment attribute is defined on the IpPort or Ip components. frDteStDlciRgLinkTable.name: frDteStDlciRgLinkTable
frDteStDlciRgLinkTable.description: This group provides the link between a Dlci and a remoteGroup.

frDteStDlciLinkToRemoteGroup.name: frDteStDlciLinkToRemoteGroup
frDteStDlciLinkToRemoteGroup.description: This attribute associates a StDlci component with a Rg component. Provisioned StDlci components must be linked to a Rg component which is under the same FrDte component.

frDteStDlciHqRowStatusTable.name: frDteStDlciHqRowStatusTable
frDteStDlciHqRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteStDlciHq components.

frDteStDlciHqRowStatusEntry.name: frDteStDlciHqRowStatusEntry
frDteStDlciHqRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteStDlciHq component.

frDteStDlciHqRowStatus.name: frDteStDlciHqRowStatus
frDteStDlciHqRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteStDlciHq components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteStDlciHqComponentName.name: frDteStDlciHqComponentName
frDteStDlciHqComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteStDlciHqStorageType.name: frDteStDlciHqStorageType
frDteStDlciHqStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteStDlciHq tables.

frDteStDlciHqIndex.name: frDteStDlciHqIndex
frDteStDlciHqIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteStDlciHq tables.

frDteStDlciHqProvTable.name: frDteStDlciHqProvTable
frDteStDlciHqProvTable.description: This group contains the Link Emission Queue provisioned attributes.

frDteStDlciHqMaxPackets.name: frDteStDlciHqMaxPackets
frDteStDlciHqMaxPackets.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of packets allowed in the Leq before being discarded. If this attribute is set to zero then the maximum number of packets is calculated from the transmit data rate. This calculated value is placed in queuePktThreshold.

frDteStDlciHqMaxMsecData.name: frDteStDlciHqMaxMsecData
frDteStDlciHqMaxMsecData.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of 'Milliseconds worth of data' allowed in the Leq before packets are discarded. The queueByteThreshold will be calculated from this attribute, based on the transmit data rate.

frDteStDlciHqMaxPercentMulticast.name: frDteStDlciHqMaxPercentMulticast
frDteStDlciHqMaxPercentMulticast.description: This attribute specifies the maximum percentage of multicast packets allowed in the Leq, based on queuePktThreshold, before being discarded. The calculated value will be placed in queueMulticastThreshold.

frDteStDlciHqTimeToLive.name: frDteStDlciHqTimeToLive
frDteStDlciHqTimeToLive.description: This attribute specifies the 'Milliseconds Time To Live' of packets in the Leq. If the timeToLive of a packet expires, it will be discarded.

frDteStDlciHqStatsTable.name: frDteStDlciHqStatsTable
frDteStDlciHqStatsTable.description: This group contains HibernationQueue general statistics.

frDteStDlciHqTimedOutPkt.name: frDteStDlciHqTimedOutPkt
frDteStDlciHqTimedOutPkt.description: This attribute counts the number of packets that have been discarded due to exceeding the timeToLive. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqQueuePurgeDiscards.name: frDteStDlciHqQueuePurgeDiscards
frDteStDlciHqQueuePurgeDiscards.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets discarded by a queue purge which occurs when the Dlci goes down. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqTStatsTable.name: frDteStDlciHqTStatsTable
frDteStDlciHqTStatsTable.description: This group contains Link Emission Queue total statistics.

frDteStDlciHqTotalPktHandled.name: frDteStDlciHqTotalPktHandled
frDteStDlciHqTotalPktHandled.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets handled by the Leq. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqTotalPktForwarded.name: frDteStDlciHqTotalPktForwarded
frDteStDlciHqTotalPktForwarded.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets forwarded by the Leq. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqTotalPktQueued.name: frDteStDlciHqTotalPktQueued
frDteStDlciHqTotalPktQueued.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets that required queuing by the Leq due to transmit congestion. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqTotalMulticastPkt.name: frDteStDlciHqTotalMulticastPkt
frDteStDlciHqTotalMulticastPkt.description: This attribute counts the total number of multicast packets handled by this instance of FrDte. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqTotalPktDiscards.name: frDteStDlciHqTotalPktDiscards
frDteStDlciHqTotalPktDiscards.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets that were discarded for this instance of FrDte. This is the sum of timedOutPkt, forcedPktDiscards, queuePurgeDiscards, pktThresholdExceeded, byteThresholdExceeded, mulThresholdExceeded and memThresholdExceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqCStatsTable.name: frDteStDlciHqCStatsTable
frDteStDlciHqCStatsTable.description: This group contains Link Emission Queue current statistics.

frDteStDlciHqCurrentPktQueued.name: frDteStDlciHqCurrentPktQueued
frDteStDlciHqCurrentPktQueued.description: This attribute contains the current number of packets queued.

frDteStDlciHqCurrentBytesQueued.name: frDteStDlciHqCurrentBytesQueued
frDteStDlciHqCurrentBytesQueued.description: This attribute contains the current number of bytes queued.

frDteStDlciHqCurrentMulticastQueued.name: frDteStDlciHqCurrentMulticastQueued
frDteStDlciHqCurrentMulticastQueued.description: This attribute counts the current number of multicast packets in the queue.

frDteStDlciHqThrStatsTable.name: frDteStDlciHqThrStatsTable
frDteStDlciHqThrStatsTable.description: This group contains Link Emission Queue threshold statistics.

frDteStDlciHqQueuePktThreshold.name: frDteStDlciHqQueuePktThreshold
frDteStDlciHqQueuePktThreshold.description: This attribute is the maximum number of packets that can be contained in the queue before being discarded. If maxPackets was set to 0 then this attribute will contain the value that has been calculated based on the transmit data rate. If maxPackets was set to one or more than this attribute will contain that number.

frDteStDlciHqPktThresholdExceeded.name: frDteStDlciHqPktThresholdExceeded
frDteStDlciHqPktThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to the queuePktThreshold being exceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqQueueByteThreshold.name: frDteStDlciHqQueueByteThreshold
frDteStDlciHqQueueByteThreshold.description: This attribute is the maximum number of bytes allowed in the queue based on maxMsecData and the transmit data rate.

frDteStDlciHqByteThresholdExceeded.name: frDteStDlciHqByteThresholdExceeded
frDteStDlciHqByteThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to the queueByteThreshold being exceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqQueueMulticastThreshold.name: frDteStDlciHqQueueMulticastThreshold
frDteStDlciHqQueueMulticastThreshold.description: This attribute is the number of multicast packets allowed in the queue based on maxPercentMulticast and maxPackets.

frDteStDlciHqMulThresholdExceeded.name: frDteStDlciHqMulThresholdExceeded
frDteStDlciHqMulThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to the queueMulticastThreshold being exceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteStDlciHqMemThresholdExceeded.name: frDteStDlciHqMemThresholdExceeded
frDteStDlciHqMemThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to exceeding the memory usage threshold for Leq. The memory usage threshold is determined by the Leq software, guaranteeing that the Leq does not consume all of the memory. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqRowStatusTable.name: frDteLeqRowStatusTable
frDteLeqRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteLeq components.

frDteLeqRowStatusEntry.name: frDteLeqRowStatusEntry
frDteLeqRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteLeq component.

frDteLeqRowStatus.name: frDteLeqRowStatus
frDteLeqRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteLeq components. These components can be added and deleted.

frDteLeqComponentName.name: frDteLeqComponentName
frDteLeqComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteLeqStorageType.name: frDteLeqStorageType
frDteLeqStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteLeq tables.

frDteLeqIndex.name: frDteLeqIndex
frDteLeqIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteLeq tables.

frDteLeqProvTable.name: frDteLeqProvTable
frDteLeqProvTable.description: This group contains the Link Emission Queue provisioned attributes.

frDteLeqMaxMsecData.name: frDteLeqMaxMsecData
frDteLeqMaxMsecData.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of 'Milliseconds worth of data' allowed in the Leq before packets are discarded. The queueByteThreshold will be calculated from this attribute, based on the transmit data rate.

frDteLeqStatsTable.name: frDteLeqStatsTable

frDteLeqTimedOutPkt.name: frDteLeqTimedOutPkt
frDteLeqTimedOutPkt.description: This attribute counts the number of packets that have been discarded due to exceeding the timeToLive. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqHardwareForcedPkt.name: frDteLeqHardwareForcedPkt
frDteLeqHardwareForcedPkt.description: This attribute counts the number of hardware forced packets on this instance of FrDte. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqForcedPktDiscards.name: frDteLeqForcedPktDiscards
frDteLeqForcedPktDiscards.description: This attribute counts the total number of hardware forced packets that had to be discarded due to link failure. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqQueuePurgeDiscards.name: frDteLeqQueuePurgeDiscards
frDteLeqQueuePurgeDiscards.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets discarded by a queue purge (i.e. a discarding of all packets on the queue). This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqTStatsTable.name: frDteLeqTStatsTable
frDteLeqTStatsTable.description: This group contains Link Emission Queue total statistics.

frDteLeqTotalPktHandled.name: frDteLeqTotalPktHandled
frDteLeqTotalPktHandled.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets handled by the Leq. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqTotalPktForwarded.name: frDteLeqTotalPktForwarded
frDteLeqTotalPktForwarded.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets forwarded by the Leq. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqTotalPktQueued.name: frDteLeqTotalPktQueued
frDteLeqTotalPktQueued.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets that required queuing by the Leq due to transmit congestion. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqTotalMulticastPkt.name: frDteLeqTotalMulticastPkt
frDteLeqTotalMulticastPkt.description: This attribute counts the total number of multicast packets handled by this instance of FrDte. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqTotalPktDiscards.name: frDteLeqTotalPktDiscards
frDteLeqTotalPktDiscards.description: This attribute counts the total number of packets that were discarded for this instance of FrDte. This is the sum of timedOutPkt, forcedPktDiscards, queuePurgeDiscards, pktThresholdExceeded, byteThresholdExceeded, mulThresholdExceeded and memThresholdExceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqCStatsTable.name: frDteLeqCStatsTable
frDteLeqCStatsTable.description: This group contains Link Emission Queue current statistics.

frDteLeqCurrentPktQueued.name: frDteLeqCurrentPktQueued
frDteLeqCurrentPktQueued.description: This attribute contains the current number of packets queued.

frDteLeqCurrentBytesQueued.name: frDteLeqCurrentBytesQueued
frDteLeqCurrentBytesQueued.description: This attribute contains the current number of bytes queued.

frDteLeqCurrentMulticastQueued.name: frDteLeqCurrentMulticastQueued
frDteLeqCurrentMulticastQueued.description: This attribute counts the current number of multicast packets in the queue.

frDteLeqThrStatsTable.name: frDteLeqThrStatsTable
frDteLeqThrStatsTable.description: This group contains Link Emission Queue threshold statistics.

frDteLeqQueuePktThreshold.name: frDteLeqQueuePktThreshold
frDteLeqQueuePktThreshold.description: This attribute is the maximum number of packets that can be contained in the queue before being discarded. If maxPackets was set to 0 then this attribute will contain the value that has been calculated based on the transmit data rate. If maxPackets was set to one or more than this attribute will contain that number.

frDteLeqPktThresholdExceeded.name: frDteLeqPktThresholdExceeded
frDteLeqPktThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to the queuePktThreshold being exceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqQueueByteThreshold.name: frDteLeqQueueByteThreshold
frDteLeqQueueByteThreshold.description: This attribute is the maximum number of bytes allowed in the queue based on maxMsecData and the transmit data rate.

frDteLeqByteThresholdExceeded.name: frDteLeqByteThresholdExceeded
frDteLeqByteThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to the queueByteThreshold being exceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqQueueMulticastThreshold.name: frDteLeqQueueMulticastThreshold
frDteLeqQueueMulticastThreshold.description: This attribute is the number of multicast packets allowed in the queue based on maxPercentMulticast and maxPackets.

frDteLeqMulThresholdExceeded.name: frDteLeqMulThresholdExceeded
frDteLeqMulThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to the queueMulticastThreshold being exceeded. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteLeqMemThresholdExceeded.name: frDteLeqMemThresholdExceeded
frDteLeqMemThresholdExceeded.description: This attribute counts the number of packets discarded due to exceeding the memory usage threshold for Leq. The memory usage threshold is determined by the Leq software, guaranteeing that the Leq does not consume all of the memory. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciRowStatusTable.name: frDteDlciRowStatusTable
frDteDlciRowStatusTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This entry controls the addition and deletion of frDteDlci components.

frDteDlciRowStatusEntry.name: frDteDlciRowStatusEntry
frDteDlciRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single frDteDlci component.

frDteDlciRowStatus.name: frDteDlciRowStatus
frDteDlciRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of frDteDlci components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

frDteDlciComponentName.name: frDteDlciComponentName
frDteDlciComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

frDteDlciStorageType.name: frDteDlciStorageType
frDteDlciStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the frDteDlci tables.

frDteDlciIndex.name: frDteDlciIndex
frDteDlciIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the frDteDlci tables.

frDteDlciStateTable.name: frDteDlciStateTable
frDteDlciStateTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

frDteDlciAdminState.name: frDteDlciAdminState
frDteDlciAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

frDteDlciOperationalState.name: frDteDlciOperationalState
frDteDlciOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

frDteDlciUsageState.name: frDteDlciUsageState
frDteDlciUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

frDteDlciOperTable.name: frDteDlciOperTable
frDteDlciOperTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group contains the operational attributes for the Dlci component.

frDteDlciDlciState.name: frDteDlciDlciState
frDteDlciDlciState.description: This attribute reflects the current operational circuit state of the Dlci. The state active indicates that the circuit is up and inactive that the circuit is down. The state invalid means the circuit has been deleted by the DCE (via Lmi).

frDteDlciLastTimeChange.name: frDteDlciLastTimeChange
frDteDlciLastTimeChange.description: The last time dlciState changed state.

frDteDlciSentFrames.name: frDteDlciSentFrames
frDteDlciSentFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted across the interface. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciSentOctets.name: frDteDlciSentOctets
frDteDlciSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciReceivedFrames.name: frDteDlciReceivedFrames
frDteDlciReceivedFrames.description: Number of frames received across the interface. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciReceivedOctets.name: frDteDlciReceivedOctets
frDteDlciReceivedOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciReceivedFECNs.name: frDteDlciReceivedFECNs
frDteDlciReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames with the FECN bit set received from the network. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciReceivedBECNs.name: frDteDlciReceivedBECNs
frDteDlciReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames with the BECN bit set received from the network. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciDiscardedFrames.name: frDteDlciDiscardedFrames
frDteDlciDiscardedFrames.description: The number of inbound frames dropped because of format errors, or because the VC was inactive. This counter will wrap around to 0 when it exceeds its maximum count.

frDteDlciCreationType.name: frDteDlciCreationType
frDteDlciCreationType.description: This indicates whether the virtual circuit was manually created (static), or dynamically created (dynamic) via the data link control management interface.

frDteDlciCreationTime.name: frDteDlciCreationTime
frDteDlciCreationTime.description: The time when the circuit was created, whether by the Data Link Connection Management Interface or by an SNMP set request.

frDteDlciRateEnforcement.name: frDteDlciRateEnforcement
frDteDlciRateEnforcement.description: This attribute specifies whether the CIR attributes committedInformationRate, committedBurst, and excessBurst are used to define rate enforcement on this user DLCI. If rateEnforcement is enabled, and the combined Committed and Excess burst thresholds are exceeded, the frame in violation will be discarded immediately if a HibernationQueue subcomponent is not provisioned under the StDlci component (static entries only). If a HibernationQueue is provisioned, the frame will be placed on the HibernationQueue at time of violation and transmission will be attempted later after the point at which the burst thresholds will no longer be exceeded. Setting all the CIR attributes to zero has the same affect as setting this attribute to disabled. Setting this attribute will operationally override the corresponding provisional value on static entries.

frDteDlciCommittedInformationRate.name: frDteDlciCommittedInformationRate
frDteDlciCommittedInformationRate.description: The average number of bits to be transferred per second over the DLCI to the DCE. When this attribute is set to zero, the link speed will be used instead. Setting this attribute will operationally override the corresponding provisional value on static entries.

frDteDlciCommittedBurst.name: frDteDlciCommittedBurst
frDteDlciCommittedBurst.description: The committed burst size (in bits) to which the DLCI wants to subscribe. Setting this attribute will operationally override the corresponding provisional value on static entries.

frDteDlciExcessBurst.name: frDteDlciExcessBurst
frDteDlciExcessBurst.description: The excess burst size (in bits) to which the DLCI wants to subscribe. Setting this attribute will operationally override the corresponding provisional value on static entries.

frDteDlciExcessBurstAction.name: frDteDlciExcessBurstAction
frDteDlciExcessBurstAction.description: This attribute specifies the action taken when the committedBurst size has been exceeded on the Dlci but the excessBurst size has not. If the attribute is set to setDeBit, the Discard Eligibility bit in the Frame Relay header will be turned on. If the attribute is set to none, no action will be taken. Setting this attribute will operationally override the corresponding provisional value on static entries.
